value.title: 'What the hell is wrong with them?': Biden rips Republicans for refusing to don masks during siege
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden is taking aim at some Republican members of Congress who refused to wear masks while huddling in secure rooms last week during the storming of the Capitol.

value.title: FBI agent in Trump-Russia's request for 'validation' of Steele reporting denied, left Crossfire Hurricane
value.excerpt: An agent involved in the FBI’s original Trump-Russia case left the Crossfire Hurricane team amid a “professional disagreement” with Bill Priestap, after the former assistant director of counterintelligence denied his request for an “enhanced validation review” of Christopher Steele’s reporting.

value.title: Cuomo takes parting shot at Trump admin, targets 'reclamation' of SALT funds
value.excerpt: The SALT cap has been one of the bigger thorns in Cuomo's side in recent years.

value.title: VP-elect Harris compares Capitol riots to 2017 'Unite the Right' rally
value.excerpt: Vice President-Elect Kamala Harris said Thursday that last week's assault on the U.S. Capitol reminded her of the 2017 "Unite the Right" rally in Charlottesville, Va.

value.title: Pence front and center in Capitol siege aftermath
value.excerpt: Vice President Mike Pence flew to West Virginia on Friday to attend and speak at a public celebration for the late Air Force Brig. Gen. Chuck Yeager.

value.title: Rose McGowan calls Trump's second impeachment 'cult propaganda,' 'a theater of mass distraction'
value.excerpt: In a scathing tweet, McGowan called the actions against Trump cultlike which is something she's said numerous times in the past about Hollywood. "This impeachment is Cult propaganda. A theater of mass distraction.

value.title: Twitter introduces @SecondGentleman handle for incoming Biden administration
value.excerpt: Twitter is introducing a new handle for the first-ever husband of a vice president as it begins transferring official White House social media accounts to the incoming Biden administration.

value.title: Biden's $1.9T stimulus plan is a 'bailout' for blue states' bad lockdown policies: Waltz
value.excerpt: Rep. Michael Waltz, R-Fla., took issue Friday with President-elect Joe Biden's massive $1.9 trillion stimulus package proposal that aims to combat the coronavirus and attempt to pump up a U.S. economy severely battered by the worst pandemic to strike the globe in a century.

value.title: Dan Scavino tells Trump officials to be ‘proud’ of accomplishments
value.excerpt: As the Trump administration heads into its final week, White House spokesman Dan Scavino told administration officials Thursday to hold their "heads high" and be "proud" of their accomplishments" despite "cancel culture."

value.title: Wyoming GOP rips Rep. Liz Cheney for voting to impeach Trump
value.excerpt: Wyoming Republican leaders said Cheney’s decision led to a “whirlwind” of criticism in her home state.

value.title: Colorado officials balk at Trump decision to move Space Command HQ to Alabama
value.excerpt: Officials in Colorado Springs are slamming the Trump administration’s decision to move U.S. Space Command from its temporary location in their city to Alabama claiming the move was based on President Trump’s “personal interest,” but Fox News has learned that Air Force Secretary Barbara Barrett made the

value.title: Arizona GOP Gov. Ducey says Biden 'a good man' who 'wants to serve his country'
value.excerpt: Arizona’s Republican Gov. Doug Ducey, one of a dwindling number of GOP lawmakers in the Copper State, said Thursday that President-elect Biden is a “good man” and he looks forward to working with him.

value.title: Rep. Marjorie Taylor Greene vows to file articles of impeachment against Biden
value.excerpt: Rep. Marjorie Taylor Greene, the newly elected Republican from Georgia, took to Twitter Wednesday to announce that she will be filing articles of impeachment against President-elect Joe Biden shortly after he takes office.

value.title: Swalwell compares Trump to Usama bin Laden: 'He was responsible'
value.excerpt: Democratic California Rep. Eric Swalwell, who remains on the House Intelligence Committee despite foggy ties to a spy for China and who will serve as an impeachment manager, associated President Trump with Usama bin Laden in an interview Tuesday.

value.title: Maxine Waters warns Trump 'capable of starting a civil war'
value.excerpt: Rep. Maxine Waters, D-Calif., urged the House of Representatives to impeach President Trump on Wednesday, arguing that he was "the worst president in the history of the United States."

value.title: Cindy McCain trades shots with top AZ Republican over Biden endorsement
value.excerpt: Cindy McCain, widow of the late GOP Sen. John McCain, fired back at the state's Republican Party on Tuesday following the announcement of a resolution to censure her over supposed ties to leftist, globalist causes and failure to support President Trump.

value.title: Trump calls on Americans, Big Tech to help ensure peaceful transition: 'NO violence'
value.excerpt: EXCLUSIVE: President Trump on Wednesday is calling for "all Americans" to help "ease tensions and calm tempers," saying he does "not" stand for violence "of any kind" -- and he's asking Big Tech to join the effort.

value.title: 'Squad' member accuses VP of 'cowardice' for not using 25th Amendment to remove Trump
value.excerpt: Rep. Ayanna Pressley, D-Mass., said Vice President Mike Pence's decision not to invoke the 25th Amendment to remove President Trump from office is a show of "pure cowardice."

value.title: Biden names Obama-era UN ambassador Samantha Power to lead USAID
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden announced that former U.S. Ambassador to the United Nations Samantha Power will be his nominee for administrator of the United States Agency for International Development (USAID), a position that now will be added to the National Security Council.

value.title: Pence uses Pelosi's own words to justify not invoking the 25th Amendment
value.excerpt: Vice President Mike Pence told Speaker of the House Nancy Pelosi that he will not invoke the 25th Amendment, as lawmakers flooded into the House chamber for a vote Tuesday night on a resolution calling for him to do so.

value.title: Kamala Harris' Vogue cover defended by Anna Wintour amid controversy
value.excerpt: Vogue editor-in-chief Anna Wintour has spoken out after the magazine's cover shoot featuring Vice President-elect Kamala Harris received backlash.

value.title: Biden campaign bundlers to score senior White House positions
value.excerpt: At least eight top Biden campaign bundlers will be appointed or nominated to senior White House positions, according to a Fox News count.

value.title: Rep. Kevin McCarthy is open to censuring Trump: source
value.excerpt: House Minority Leader Kevin McCarthy is open to censuring President Trump, a source familiar with his thinking told Fox News Tuesday.

value.title: Miranda Devine: Dems 'hatred' for Trump supporters is 'un-American'
value.excerpt: Fox News contributor Miranda Devine said Tuesday the rhetoric used against President Trump's supporters after the Capitol riots are dividing the country further.

value.title: Easy for Joe Biden to 'heal' country with opposition silenced on social media: Dave Rubin
value.excerpt: Big Tech censorship of President Trump and conservatives needs to be addressed now, or soon everyone will be silenced, Dave Rubin warned Tuesday.

value.title: Biden OMB nominee Neera Tanden received $731G salary from liberal nonprofit
value.excerpt: One of President-elect Biden's top Cabinet appointees earned more than $700,000 as the head of a leading liberal nonprofit, her financial disclosures reveal.

value.title: Trump, Pence meet for 1st time since Capitol riot
value.excerpt: President Trump lashed out at Mike Pence last week after the vice president said he lacked authority under the Constitution to overturn election results on the president’s behalf.

value.title: Manchin calls second Trump impeachment bid 'ill-advised': 'Let the judicial system do its job'
value.excerpt: House Democrats' attempt to impeach President Trump for a second time in connection with last week's riot at the U.S. Capitol is "so ill-advised," Sen. Joe Manchin, D-W.Va. told "Special Report" Monday.

value.title: Critics mock NY Gov. Cuomo's sudden denunciation of lockdowns, suggest Trump hacked his Twitter account
value.excerpt: Democratic New York Gov. Andrew Cuomo raised eyebrows on Monday for his drastic shift on lockdowns during the pandemic.

value.title: Gidley blasts Democrats' 'disgusting tactic' of claiming anyone pro-Trump 'agrees with lawless thugs'
value.excerpt: Former Deputy White House Press Secretary Hogan Gidley ripped into Democrats and their supporters in Hollywood and the media Monday for making blanket claims that anyone who supports President Trump is also supportive of the "lawless thugs" who attacked the U.S. Capitol last week.
